name: sa4_g55a_tot_fam_inc_by_lbr_frc_sts_cpl_fam_wh_chld_census_2016
title: SA4-G55a Total Family Income (Weekly) by Labour Force Status of Partners for Couple Families with Children-Census 2016

legal.licenceType: Creative Commons Attribution 2.5 Australia (CC BY 2.5 AU)

keyword: census,2016,gcp,general community profile,work status,children,g55a,family income,income,couple family,labour force
abstract:
SA4 based data for Total Family Income (Weekly) by Labour Force Status of Parents/Partners for Couple Families With Children, in General Community Profile (GCP), 2016 Census. Count of couple families with children. 'Employed, worked full-time' is defined as having worked 35 hours or more in all jobs during the week prior to Census Night. Employed, away from work' comprises employed persons who did not work any hours in the week prior to Census Night or who did not state their number of hours worked. G55 is broken up into two sections (G55a-G55b) this section contains 'Negative Nil income Both employed Worked Full-time' - '$4000 or more One employed Part-time Other not working'. The data is by SA4 2016 boundaries. Periodicity: 5-Yearly.
Note: There are small random adjustments made to all cell values to protect the confidentiality of data. These adjustments may cause the sum of rows or columns to differ by small amounts from table totals.
For more information visit the data source: http://www.abs.gov.au/census.
